metadata.description:
Niels and the team brainstorm about the current understanding of behavior and hierarchical structure. Jeff presents how leveraging hierarchy could enable rapid construction of multi-modal models. Viviane highlights edge cases that challenge our existing behavioral framework.

00:00 Introduction and Initial Thoughts
03:42 Model Sharing and Learning Challenges
08:59 Hierarchy and Learning Models
55:39 Forgetting Lower-Level Representations
56:48 Analyzing the Thousand Brains Logo
58:44 Viviane's Presentation on Sensorimotor Patches
01:05:35 Challenges in Modeling Object Deformation
